brewery.brewery_description:
The 5 Lamps Dublin Brewery was set up in early 2012 and the first beer The 5 Lamps Dublin Lager was launched in September 2012. Though originally intended for North Strand, hence the name, the brewery's first location was in Donore Avenue Dublin 8. In 2019 it moved to the former Camden Deluxe Hotel.

The core range is brewed by parent company C&C in Clonmel, with specials and seasonals coming from the Camden Street site.

William Harvey is the head brewer. William enjoyed a 26 year career with Guinness across a number of functions including but not limited to: Brewer, Technical manager for the US and Canada and Head of Procurement for brewing materials and brewing sites. William is passionate about beer and has forgotten more about beer in his lifetime than most people are likely to know

beer.beer_description:
Brewed with an assemblage of malts, this porter expresses authenticity and freshness, with a great body and great colour due to the generosity of the Chocolate malt and Roast barley blend used in brewing. With a complexity of aromas including dark chocolate and toasted malts, against a toffee and caramel background and a soft rounded hop note to deliver a long lingering finish.
This is a beer with a message and the message is ‘More’!

Blackpitts Porter has a dark ruby colour, is wonderfully finished and has a great personality.
We’ve rebrewed our Blackpitts Porter to achieve a rich and creamy pint with the same complex aromas, but with a smooth velvety texture.
